A view of the headquarters of Bytedance in Beijing in December 2018 Photo: ICÂ China's tech firm ByteDance has reportedly begun investing in the mobile security sector through an investment in Track View, which offers a cross-platform app that connects users' mobile devices to a mobile security system.One of ByteDance's subsidiaries, translated as Beijing Liangzi Yuedong Technology Co, has launched an investment in Track View, which is based in Suzhou, East China's Jiangsu Province, according to Chinese enterprises information provider tianyancha.com.Track View offers users multiple mobile security services, including location tracking, video and audio monitoring, instant alerts and remote recording, said Track View's website.Information security is critical and always comes first for a company like ByteDance, Li Chengdong, a Beijing-based industry analyst, told the Global Times on Tuesday.ByteDance's shoring up of related sectors is a necessary step, Li said, noting that this could be realized either through investment or through independent research and development.According to Track View's official account on China's Twitter-like social media platform Weibo, it also offers TeamLink, an online service for web conferences.ByteDance is an internet technology company founded in Beijing in 2012, with popular products including the online content platform Toutiao and the short video platform Tik Tok.Its products and services now cover 150 countries and regions in 75 languages, according to ByteDance's website.ByteDance had not replied to the Global Times as of press time. 
